quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  30,31,"(Set your face steadfastly for the Deen) turning to Him (Allah) alone. And fear Him, establish the Prayer and be not of those who worship others besides Him"
  30,32,"(And be not) of those who split up their Deen, and become sects — every group happy with what they have"
  30,33,"And when any harm affects the people, they pray to their Lord, turning to Him alone. Then no sooner He lets them taste of His Grace, than do some of them revert to worshiping others besides Him"
  30,34,To show their ingratitude for what We have given them! Enjoy for now! You will then soon come to know (the inevitable consequence of your ingratitude)
  30,35,Have We ever sent down to them any authority to speak for what they worship besides Allah
  30,36,"And when We let people taste something good by Our Grace they rejoice at it. But if adversity afflicts them because of their past deeds, then and there, they despair"
  30,37,"Have they not seen that Allah gives the provision in ample measure to whom He wills and restricts it to whom He wills? In that, indeed, are signs for people who believe"
  30,38,"Give then to the relative his right, and to the needy, and the traveller. This is best for those who seek Allah's pleasure. And they are the ones truly successful"
  30,39,"And what you give for profit so that the increase is at the cost of other people's amwaal (property, dues) then it is not a lawful increase/profit with Allah. And what you give in charity seeking Allah's pleasure — the givers of such charity are the ones who will get their return multiplied"
  30,40,"Allah is He Who has created you, then provided you with sustenance, then causes you to die, and then brings you back to life. Are there any of those whom you worship besides Allah who can do any of these things? Glorified and exalted is He above all those whom they worship besides Him"
  30,41,"Corruption has appeared in the land and the sea — because of what people did — to let them taste some consequence of what they do, so that they might return to the Right Path"
  30,42,"Say, \"Travel on the earth and notice what happened in the end to people who lived before you. Most of them worshiped others besides Allah"
  30,43,"Set your face resolutely for the Deen (way of life) established (by Allah for mankind), before the Inevitable Day comes from Allah. On that Day people will segregate"
  30,44,"He who rejects the Truth, the responsibility for that rejection shall lie on him himself. And all those who do good deeds, they are making a good preparation for themselves"
  30,45,"So that He may, by His Grace, reward those who believe and do good deeds. He does not indeed love those who suppress the Truth"
  30,46,"And among His signs is that He sends the winds heralding good news (of rains), so that He might give you a taste of His Grace, that ships might sail at His Command, that you might seek His Favour, and that you might be grateful"
  30,47,"And, before you, We did send Messengers to their respective peoples. And they came to them with clear signs. Then We punished the criminals. And it was incumbent on Us to help the believers"
  30,48,"Allah is the One Who sends the winds. Then the interaction of the winds raises a cloud. Then He spreads the cloud across the sky as He pleases, and breaks it into fragments. Then you see the rain pouring down from within them. And when He makes the rain fall on whomsoever of His creatures He pleases, those creatures do then rejoice"
  30,49,"And they were indeed in despair, before it (the rain) was sent down upon them"
  30,50,"Look then at these results of Allah's Mercy — how He gives life to the earth after it had been dead. Indeed, that (Mercy) surely shall give life to the Dead. And He is the One capable of doing anything"
  30,51,"And if We send a wind and they see it (the green earth) turn yellow (giving man its yield), verily, they still continue ungratefully to disbelieve (in Allah's Mercy)"
  30,52,"And you cannot indeed make the dead hear, nor can you make the deaf hear the call when they turn their backs and go away"
  30,53,"And, nor can you advise the blind out of their straying. You can make none to hear except those who believe in Our Verses/signs and then submit"